Interface Mergeable<T extends Mergeable<T>>


  • public interface Mergeable<T extends Mergeable<T>>
    A merge is an object which knows how to combine two objects of the same type into a composite object containing features from both inputs.

      • reduce

        static <T extends Mergeable<T>> java.util.List<T> reduce(java.util.List<T> mergables)
        Takes a collection of Mergeables and allows one to add new elements to a running collection of objects. If the a new object which doesn't meet the mergeable(Mergeable) criteria the window is flushed via reducing against mergeLeft(Mergeable). The element is then inserted into the now empty window.

        Merge check respecting one side or the other being null. This is to say this method checks whether either the left or right element is null or if the elements are mergeable(Mergeable).
